HEADWORD: Hellhound
<hw>Hell"hound`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>hellehund</ets>.]</ety> <def>A dog of hell; an agent of
hell.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>hellhound</qex>, that doth hunt us all to death.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hellier</ent>⟦br⟧
